  "texts": [
    "Deictic relations P involves perspectives P x y,",
    ", which implies x perceives y (or person A perceives person B).",
    "Using these relational frames, we can describe the complex concept \"I see you\" i.e., perspective-taking ToM.",
    "For example, perspective-taking such as feeling someone's pain (that would be important for AI to develop compassion as a human does), may involve C A B, A simple schematic illustration of how perspective-taking ToM (\"I see\") involves the combination of several relational frames to build a hierarchical perspective-taking event of another person.",
    "Edwards 10.3389/fncom.2024.1395901 Frontiers in Computational Neuroscience 17 frontiersin.org"
  ]
